nancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20healthcare%20providers%20in%20Alabama%20have%20already%20halted%20IVF%20programs%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20ruling%2C%20given%20that%20IVF%20treatments%20may%20include%20the%20discarding%20of%20fertilized%20eggs%2C%20which%20may%20now%20violate%20the%20state's%20Wrongful%20Death%20of%20a%20Minor%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20an%20IVF%20exception%20is%20notable%2C%20given%20the%20carveout%20contained%20within%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F115th-congress%2Fsenate-bill%2F231%2Ftext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprevious%20version%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Life%20at%20Conception%20Act%20introduced%20by%20Republican%20Sen.%20Rand%20Paul%20of%20Kentucky%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNothing%20in%20this%20Act%20shall%20be%20construed%20to%20require%20the%20prosecution%20of%20any%20woman%20for%20the%20death%20of%20her%20unborn%20child%2C%20a%20prohibition%20on%20in%20vitro%20fertilization%2C%20or%20a%20prohibition%20on%20use%20of%20birth%20control%20or%20another%20means%20of%20preventing%20fertilization%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20the%202017%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublican%20Rep.%20Alexander%20Mooney%2C%20the%20main%20House%20sponsor%20of%20the%20bill%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20why%20that%20exception%20was%20not%20included.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20did%20spokespeople%20for%20Speaker%20Johnson%2C%20who%20largely%20controls%20the%20House%20floor%20and%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-mike-johnson-republican-speaker-house-louisiana-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevangelical%20Christian%20views%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20entailed%20staunch%20opposition%20to%20abortion%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20woman%20is%20pregnant%2C%20science%20tells%20us%20the%20new%20life%20she%20carries%20is%20a%20completely%20separate%20and%20fully%20new%20human%20being%20from%20the%20moment%20of%20fertilization%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.c-span.org%2Fvideo%2F%3F515843-1%2Fhearing-texas-abortion-law%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2021%20hearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Texas's%206-week%20abortion%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Alabama%20ruling%2C%20some%20Republicans%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-alabama-ivf-ruling-gop-republicans-2024-biden-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escrambled%20to%20declare%20their%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20IVF%20treatments%2C%20recognizing%20the%20unpopularity%20of%20any%20potential%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20GOP%20Senate%20candidates%20in%20competitive%20battleground%20states%2C%20who%20quickly%20moved%20to%20issue%20pro-IVF%20statements%20on%20Friday%20with%20the%20encouragement%20of%20Senate%20Republicans'%20campaign%20arm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20House%20Republicans%20in%20swing%20seats%20who%20have%20previously%20cosponsored%20the%20Life%20at%20Conception%20Act%20have%20done%20the%20same%2C%20including%20current%20cosponsor%20Reps.%20Michelle%20Steel%20of%20California%20and%20past%20cosponsor%20David%20Schweikert%20of%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20someone%20who%20struggled%20to%20get%20pregnant%2C%20I%20believe%20all%20life%20is%20a%20gift.%20IVF%20allowed%20me%2C%20as%20it%20has%20so%20many%20others%2C%20to%20start%C2%A0my%20family.%20I%20believe%20there%20is%20nothing%20more%20pro-life%20than%20helping%20families%20have%20children%2C%20and%20I%20do%20not%20support%20federal%20restrictions%20on%20IVF.%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Rep.%20Michelle%20Steel%20(%40RepSteel)%