ny%20site%2C%20instead%20of%20his%20own%20photo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20then%20searched%20through%20the%20profile%20and%20found%20the%20phone%20number%2C%20which%20belonged%20to%20the%20anchor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20contacted%20the%20anchor%20through%20an%20instant%20messaging%20app%20but%20was%20informed%20by%20him%20that%20some%20unknown%20person%20had%20used%20his%20photo%20and%20created%20a%20fake%20account%20on%20the%20matrimony%20site%2C%20and%20that%20he%20had%20lodged%20a%20complaint%20in%20the%20Cyber%20Crime%20police%20station%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20woman%20continued%20to%20send%20messages%20to%20the%20anchor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20blocked%20her%20number%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%2C%20who%20was%20determined%20to%20marry%20the%20anchor%2C%20planned%20to%20kidnap%20him%2C%20thinking%20she%20could%20get%20things%20sorted%20out%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccordingly%2C%20she%20hired%20four%20persons%20to%20kidnap%20the%20anchor%20and%20also%20installed%20a%20tracking%20device%20on%20the%20victim's%20car%20to%20watch%20his%20movements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2011%2C%20the%20four%20hired%20men%20kidnapped%20the%20victim%20and%20took%20him%20to%20the%20office%20of%20the%20woman%20and%20beat%20him%20up%20badly%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFearing%20for%20his%20life%2C%20the%20TV%20anchor%20agreed%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20woman's%20calls%20and%20only%20then%20was%20he%20let%20off%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20later%20lodged%20a%20complaint%20with%20Uppal%20police%20station%2C%20and%20a%20case%20was%20registered%20under%20363%20(kidnapping)%2C%20341%20(wrongful%20restraint)%2C%20342%20(wrongful%20confinement)%2C%20and%20relevant%20sections%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20course%20of%20the%20investigation%2C%20the%20police%20arrested%20the%20accused%20woman%20along%20with%20the%20four%20men%20she%