mate-crisis-is-foundation-of-indian-farmers-protests%2F%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20peaceful%20civil%20society%20protest%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20worth%20remembering%20that%20agriculture%20was%20also%20a%20critical%20issue%20for%20the%20nation%20in%20its%20first%20decades.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20prime%20minister%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20bluntly%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceverything%20can%20wait%2C%20but%20not%20agriculture%E2%80%9D.%20This%20line%20of%20thinking%20eventually%20led%20to%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20of%20the%20late%201960s%2C%20forging%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20security%20and%20providing%20much-needed%20revenue%20for%20some%20of%20its%20farmers.%20But%20back%20in%20the%20present%2C%20a%20looming%20water%20crisis%20has%20returned%20Indian%20agriculture%20to%20the%20spotlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFarmers%E2%80%99%20grievances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20harnessed%20high-yield%20grain%20varieties%2C%20water-intensive%20practices%20(largely%20reliant%20on%20pumped%20groundwater)%20and%20heavy%20fertiliser%20use.%20Understanding%20that%20such%20investments%20would%20not%20be%20made%20by%20farmers%20without%20a%20guaranteed%20market%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fwhat-is-the-basis-of-msp-6609668%2F%5C%22%3Ecreated%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0a%20minimum%20support%20price%20(MSP)%20for%20wheat%20in%201966-67.%20This%20set%20a%20base%20price%20for%20government%20procurement%20at%20a%20certain%20percentage%20above%20input%20costs%2C%20and%20therefore%20guaranteed%20farmers%20an%20assured%20buyer%3A%20even%20if%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20crop%20was%20not%20bought%20by%20the%20government%2C%20the%20MSP%20set%20a%20floor%20price%20for%20other%20buyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20MSP%20regime%20covers%2023%20crops%3A%20varieties%20of%20cereals%2C%20pulses%20and%20some%20cash%20crops%20like%20sugarcane%20and%20cotton.%20It%20has%20been%20very%20successful%20in%20incentivising%20food%20production.%20So%2C%20instead%20of%20having%20to%20import%20grain%20as%20was%20the%20case%20before%20the%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20by%202017%20India%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feands.da.gov.in%2FPDF%2FAt%2520a%2520Glance%25202019%2520Eng.pdf%5C%22%3Ewas%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20first-largest%20global%20producer%20of%20pulses%20and%20jute%20and%20the%20second-largest%20global%20producer%20of%20wheat%2C%20rice%20and%20sugarcane.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20only%20the%20MSP%20for%20sugarcane%20is%20guaranteed%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F7053%2F1%2Fessential_commodities_act_1955.pdf%5C%22%3Eunder%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20Essential%20Commodities%20Act%20of%201955.%20At%20their%20heart%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%20in%20India%20are%20a%20call%20for%20the%20MSP%20regime%20to%20be%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fagriculture%2Ffarmers-reject-centre-s-new-msp-proposal-demand-guarantee-for-all-23-crops-94546%5C%22%3Elegalised%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20many%20Indian%20farmers%2C%20this%20is%20the%20only%20guarantee%20of%20some%20level%20of%20financial%20security.%20However%2C%20the%20gains%20of%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20and%20the%20MSP%20regime%20(in%20its%20current%20form)%20are%20currently%20being%20undone%20by%20a%20series%20of%20challenges%2C%20including%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinite%20resources%20pushed%20to%20the%20brink%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%2019th-century%20India%2C%20the%20British%20viceroy%20Lord%20Curzon%20described%20the%20Indian%20economy%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20gamble%20on%20the%20monsoons%E2%80%9D.%20When%20India%20began%20extracting%20its%20groundwater%20this%20issue%20faded%2C%20but%20new%20challenges%20were%20created.%20India%20is%20now%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funesdoc.unesco.org%2Fark%3A%2F48223%2Fpf00003