overnment%20report%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-61965419%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niti.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2019-08%2FCWMI-2.0-latest.pdf%5C%22%3E74%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20area%20where%20wheat%20is%20cultivated%2C%20and%2065%25%20of%20the%20area%20where%20rice%20is%20grown%2C%20will%20face%20water%20shortages.%20The%20most%20severely%20impacted%20parts%20of%20India%20are%20the%20semi-arid%20zones%20in%20its%20north-western%20region%2C%20where%20the%20planting%20of%20wheat%20and%20paddy%20(which%20form%20the%20bulk%20of%20government%20procurement)%20is%20the%20most%20intense.%20This%20is%20where%20most%20of%20the%20protesting%20farmers%20come%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20over-extraction%20of%20groundwater%20has%20also%20led%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2073-4441%2F15%2F23%2F4125%5C%22%3Ehigher%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0concentrations%20of%20arsenic.%20This%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1809264%5C%22%3Etriggered%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0long-running%20health%20crises%20in%20states%20including%20Punjab%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%20and%20West%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20this%20focus%20on%20a%20limited%20range%20of%20crops%20means%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20indigenous%20seeds%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournalofethnicfoods.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs42779-019-0011-9%5C%22%3Edisappearing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20that%20threatens%20a%20future%20for%20India%20in%20which%20it%20may%20be%20dependent%20on%20just%20a%20few%20types%20of%20seeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20larger%20water%20crisis%20impacts%20agriculture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20context%20of%20a%20challenging%20water%20future.%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20number%20has%20taken%20off%20since%20independence%2C%20but%20its%20water%20resources%20remain%20the%20same.%20Water%20availability%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20under%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1606099%5C%22%3E1%2C486%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0cubic%20metres%20per%20person%2C%20which%20is%20alarming%20given%20that%201%2C700%20cubic%20metres%20is%20usually%20considered%20the%20benchmark%20for%20water%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20latest%20report%20on%20the%20Himalayan%20region%20by%20the%20International%20Centre%20for%20Integrated%20Mountain%20Development%20(ICIMOD)%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhkh.icimod.org%2Fhi-wise%2Fhi-wise-report%2F%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20region%20will%20hit%20%E2%80%9Cpeak%20water%E2%80%9D%20by%202050%2C%20after%20which%20water%20availability%20will%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInadequate%20government%20response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20was%20conceptualised%20at%20a%20time%20when%20India%20had%20far%20less%20resources%20to%20understand%20its%20water%20needs%2C%20but%20half%20a%20century%20later%2C%20the%20government%20has%20nothing%20new%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202020%2C%20it%20passed%20three%20farm%20laws%20that%20were%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fbilltrack%2Fthe-farm-laws-repeal-bill-2021%5C%22%3Erepealed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20November%202021.%20The%20laws%20pushed%20for%20greater%20market%20access%2C%20contract%20farming%2C%20and%20less%20regulation%20of%20essential%20commodities.%20They%20did%20not%20guarantee%20MSPs%20and%20in%20response%2C%20a%20number%20of%20state%20governments%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ftheprsblog%2Fcomparison-of-the-2020-central-farm-laws-with-the-amendments-proposed-by-states%5C%22%3Epassed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0laws%20that%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edid%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eguarantee%20MSPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weakening%20of%20the%20MSP%20regime%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20additional%20threat%20to%20the%20financial%20security%20of%20farmers%2C%20who%20are%20already%20dealing%20with%20lowered%20water%20tables%2C%20climate-induced%20floods%20and%20drought%20exacerbation%2C%20fluctuating%20monsoons%20and%20degraded%20soils%20from%20excessive%20fertiliser%20use%20%E2%80%93%20while%20these%20laws%20might%20have%20lowered%20procurement%20costs%20for%20the%20government%2C%20they%20did%20nothing%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20farming%20community%E2%80%99s%20myriad%20water%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20agricultural%20expert%20Devinder%20Sharma%20points%20out%2C%20farmers%20currently%20earn%20about%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fwatch-only-a-legally-binding-msp-can-really-help-farmers-weve-tried-all-permutations-and-combinations%5C%22%3EINR%2027%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(USD%200.33)%20per%20day%20from%20farming%3A%20they%20need%20more%20support%2C%20not%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20gained%20independence%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Bengal%20famine%20in%201943%2C%20in%20which%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2019%2Fmar%2F29%2Fwinston-churchill-policies-contributed-to-1943-bengal-famine-study%5C%22%3Emillions%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0starved%20to%20death.%20Today%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1601902%5C%22%3Ehundreds%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20millions%20reliant%20on%20agriculture%20face%20a%20catastrophic%20future%20as%20water%20availability%20dwindles.%20The%20government%20should%20know%20by%20now%20that%20everything%20can%20wait%2C%20but%20not%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Ffood%2Fanalysis-as-farmers-protest-india-must-urgently-deal-with-its-water-crisis%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2F%5C%22%3EThird%20Pole%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOmair%20Ahmad%20i