yees%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%202.8%20million%20new%20female%20subscribers%20joined%20the%20EPF%20which%20is%2011%25%20less%20compared%20to%20the%20corresponding%20period%20of%20the%20preceding%20year%20which%20stood%20at%203.14%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20of%20the%20analysis%20of%20the%20payroll%20data%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20recently%20released%20annual%20periodic%20labour%20force%20survey%20(PLFS)%20which%20showed%20that%20that%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20had%20dropped%20to%20a%20six-year%20low%20of%203.2%25%20in%20July%E2%80%93June%202022%E2%80%9323%20from%204.1%25%20in%20July%E2%80%93June%202021%E2%80%9322.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20indicated%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%2C%20the%20PLFS%20survey%20reflected%20that%20the%20share%20of%20people%20engaged%20in%20agriculture%20has%20increased%20sharply%20to%2045.8%25%20in%202022-23%20from%2045.5%25%20in%202021-22%20whereas%20the%20share%20of%20people%20engaged%20in%20manufacturing%20has%20gone%20down%20to%2011.4%25%20from%2011.6%25%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708691427000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23164554%2F42053004242_ec71ffe1ba_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fnearly-10-less-formal-jobs-created-in-2023-11-decline-in-first-time-female-employees-epfo-data%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%202023%2C%202.8%20million%20new%20female%20subscribers%20joined%20the%20EPF%20which%20is%2011%25%20less%20compared%20to%20the%20corresponding%20period%20of%20the%20preceding%20year%20which%20stood%20at%203.14%20million.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A49%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fnearly-10-less-formal-jobs-created-in-2023-11-decline-in-first-time-female-employees-epfo-data%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22France%20expels%20'rad