0Jinnah%20is%20no%20doubt%20the%20architect%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20without%20him%20Pakistan%20would%20never%20have%20been%20created%20but%2C%20very%20importantly%2C%20after%20creating%20Pakistan%20Jinnah%20had%20no%20vision%20for%20the%20country.%20Worse%2C%C2%A0%20Ahmed%20said%2C%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20very%20autocratic%20head%20of%20state%20who%20usurped%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20prime%20minister.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FcYaQdNRZkYw%3Fsi%3DTPztJoD9zWdj1-u0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221005%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%2C%20Ahmed%20refers%20to%20a%201945%20statement%20by%20Jinnah%20where%20he%20claims%20that%20democracy%2C%20constitutional%20rights%2C%20the%20economy%2C%20etc.%20all%20flow%20out%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EQuran%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Ahmed%20said%20that%20with%20this%20sort%20of%20statement%2C%20whether%20meant%20literally%20or%20intended%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20enhance%20Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20powers%2C%20there%20was%20no%20way%20Pakistan%20could%20become%20a%20modern%20secular%20democratic%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20particularly%20outspoken%20part%20of%20the%20interview%2C%20Ahmed%20said%20that%20after%20Jinnah%20the%20second%20obstacle%20that%20has%20prevented%20Pakistan%20becoming%20a%20credible%20democracy%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20has%20become%20a%20theological%20state.%20He%20said%20it%20would%20have%20to%20cease%20to%20think%20of%20itself%20as%20a%20theological%20Islamic%20state%20if%20Pakistan%20wants%20to%20develop%20into%20a%20meaningful%20and%20credible%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20death%20of%20Jinnah%2C%20Ahmed%20said%20the%20people%20who%20came%20to%20power%20in%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%93%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20Khwaja%20Najimuddin%2C%20Mohammad%20Ali%20Bogra%2C%20Mohammad%20Ali%2C%20Suhrawardy%20and%20Feroz%20Khan%20Noon%20%E2%80%93%20had%20been%20transplanted%20into%20the%20four%20provinces%20that%20created%20Pakistan%20but%20had%20no%20roots%20there.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20lacked%20the%20confidence%20to%20hold%20elections%20or%20function%20democratically%20out%20of%20fear%20they%20could%20lose%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmed%20also%20addressed%20the%20question%20why%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20army%2C%20which%20has%20the%20same%20origin%20and%20tradition%20as%20the%20Indian%20army%2C%20and%2C%20prior%20to%20independence%2C%20was%20trained%20to%20respect%20civilian%20rule%20and%20civilian%20masters%2C%20so%20frequently%20grabbed%20power%20for%20itself.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20Ahmed%20explained%20what%20made%20former%20army%20chief%20of%20Pakistan%20Ayub%20Khan%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20a%20contemporary%20of%20Indian%20army%20chiefs%20like%20K.%20M.%20Cariappa%2C%20Rajendrasinhji%20Jadeja%2C%20Satyawant%20Mallana%20Srinages%20and%20Kodandera%20Subayya%20Thimayya%20%E2%80%93%20different%20from%20his%20Indian%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%20a%20special%20question%20asked%20at%20the%20end%2C%20Ahmed%20makes%20clear%20that%20Pakistan%20is%20not%20a%20fundamentalist%20country%20and%20its%20people%20are%20not%20religious%20fanatics.%20That%20may%20be%20true%20of%20the%20government%20or%20politicians%20or%20the%20education%20system%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20true%20of%20the%20people.%20He%20also%20made%20clear%20that%20the%20people%20of%20Pakistan%20have%20enormous%20goodwill%20and%20affection%20for%20India%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20has%20experienced%20the%20same%20in%20reverse%20whenever%20he%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708682426000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23142909%2FKT-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%